Title: Entrainment and Communication with Dissipative Pseudorandom Dynamics  
Author: N. Gershenfeld G. Grinstein 
Address: Cambridge, MA 02139  Yorktown Heights, NY 10598  
Affiliation: Physics and Media Group, MIT Media Lab,  IBM Research Division, T.J. Watson Research Center,  E X  
Date: 5024 (1995)  (August 3, 1995)  
Note: Physical Review Letters 74, p.  Typeset using REVT  
Abstract: We introduce a new class of dynamical systems, analog generalizations of linear feedback shift registers, that can be designed with any number of degrees of freedom, generate optimal pseudo-random noise, and exhibit nonlinear dissipative entrainment which can be used to decode signals in communication and measurement applications. 05.45.+b, 43.72.+q 
